quran[842]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,By the (angels) ranged in ranks
  37,2,and the drivers driving
  37,3,and the reciters of the reminder
  37,4,"Verily, your God is one"
  37,5,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between the two, and the Lord of the sunrises"
  37,6,"Verily, we have adorned the lower heaven with the adornment of the stars"
  37,7,and to preserve it from every rebellious devil
  37,8,that they may not listen to the exalted chiefs; for they are hurled at from every side
  37,9,"driven off, and for them is lasting woe"
  37,10,"save such as snatches off a word, and there follows him a darting flame"
  37,11,Ask them whether they are stronger by nature or (the angels) whom we have created? We have created them of sticky clay
  37,12,"Nay, thou dost wonder and they jest"
  37,13,and when they are reminded they will not remember
  37,14,and when they see a sign they make a jest thereof
  37,15,"and say, 'This is naught but obvious sorcery"
  37,16,"What! when we are dead, and have become earth and bones, shall we then be raised"
  37,17,what! and our fathers of yore
  37,18,"Say, 'Yes, and ye shall shrink up"
  37,19,"and it shall only be one scare, and, behold, they shall look on"
  37,20,"and they shall say, 'O, woe is us! this is the day of judgment"
  37,21,"this is the day of decision, which ye did call a lie"
  37,22,"Gather ye together, ye who were unjust, with their mates and what they used to serve"
  37,23,"beside God, and guide them to the way of hell"
  37,24,"and stop them; verily, they shall be questioned"
  37,25,Why do ye not help each other
  37,26,"nay, on that day they shall resign themselves"
  37,27,"and some shall draw near to others, to question each other"
  37,28,"and they shall say, 'Verily, ye came to us from the right"
  37,29,"They shall say, 'Nay, ye were not believers"
  37,30,"nor had we any authority over you; nay, ye were an outrageous people"
  37,31,"And the sentence of our Lord shall be due for us; verily, we shall surely taste thereof"
  37,32,"we did seduce you - verily, we were erring too"
  37,33,"therefore, verily, on that day they shall share the torment"
  37,34,thus it is that we will do with the sinners
  37,35,"Verily, when it is said to them, 'There is no god but God,' they get too big with pride"
  37,36,"and say, 'What! shall we leave our gods for an infatuated poet"
  37,37,"Nay, he came with the truth, and verified the apostles"
  37,38,"verily, ye are going to taste of grievous woe"
  37,39,nor shall ye be rewarded save for that which ye have done
  37,40,Except God's sincere servants
  37,41,these shall have a stated provision
  37,42,"of fruits, and they shall be honoured"
  37,43,in the gardens of pleasure
  37,44,upon couches facing each other
  37,45,they shall be served all round with a cup from a spring
  37,46,white and delicious to those who drink
  37,47,"wherein is no insidious spirit, nor shall they be drunk therewith"
  37,48,"and with them damsels, restraining their looks, large eyed"
  37,49,as though they were a sheltered egg
  37,50,and some shall come forward to ask others
  37,51,"and a speaker amongst them shall say, 'Verily, I had a mate"
  37,52,"who used to say, \"Art thou verily of those who credit"
  37,53,"What! when we are dead, and have become earth and bones, shall we be surely judged"
  37,54,"He will say, 'Are ye looking down"
  37,55,and he shall look down and see him in the midst of hell
  37,56,"He shall say, 'By God, thou didst nearly ruin me"
  37,57,"And had it not been for the favour of my Lord, I should have been among the arraigned"
  37,58,What! shall we not die save our first death
  37,59,and shall we not be tormented
  37,60,"Verily, this is mighty bliss"
  37,61,for the like of this then let the workers work
  37,62,"Is that better as an entertainment, or the tree of Ez Zaqqum"
  37,63,"Verily, we have made it a trial to the unjust"
  37,64,"Verily, it is a tree that comes forth from the bottom of hell"
  37,65,its spathe is as it were the heads of devils
  37,66,"verily, they shall eat therefrom, and fill their bellies therefrom"
  37,67,Then shall they have upon it a mixture of boiling water
  37,68,"then, verily, their return shall be to hell"
  37,69,"Verily, they found their fathers erring"
  37,70,and they hurried on in their tracks
  37,71,but there had erred before them most of those of yore
  37,72,and we had sent warners amongst them
  37,73,"Behold, then, what was the end of those who were warned"
  37,74,save God's sincere servants
  37,75,"Noah did call upon us, and a gracious answer did we give"
  37,76,and we saved him and his people from a mighty trouble
  37,77,and we made his seed to be the survivors
  37,78,and we left for him amongst posterity
  37,79,peace upon Noah in the worlds
  37,80,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,81,"verily, he was of our believing servants"
  37,82,Then we drowned the others
  37,83,"And, verily, of his sect was Abraham"
  37,84,when he came to his Lord with a sound heart
  37,85,"when he said to his father and his people, 'What is it that ye serve"
  37,86,with a lie do ye desire gods beside God
  37,87,What then is your thought respecting the Lord of the worlds
  37,88,And he looked a look at the stars
  37,89,"and said, 'Verily, I am sick"
  37,90,and they turned their backs upon him fleeing
  37,91,"And he went aside unto their gods and said, 'Will ye not eat"
  37,92,What ails you that ye will not speak
  37,93,And he went aside to them smiting with the right hand
  37,94,And they rushed towards him
  37,95,"Said he, 'Do ye serve what ye hew out"
  37,96,"when God has created you, and what ye make"
  37,97,"Said they, 'Build for him a pyre, and throw him into the flaming hell"
  37,98,"They desired to plot against him, but we made them inferior"
  37,99,"Said he, 'Verily, I am going to my Lord, He will guide me"
  37,100,"My Lord! grant me (a son), one of the righteous"
  37,101,and we gave him glad tidings of a clement boy
  37,102,"And when he reached the age to work with him, he said, 'O my boy! verily, I have seen in a dream that I should sacrifice thee, look then what thou seest right.' Said he, 'O my sire! do what thou art bidden; thou wilt find me, if it please God, one of the patient"
  37,103,"And when they were resigned, and Abraham had thrown him down upon his forehead"
  37,104,"we called to him, 'O Abraham"
  37,105,"thou hast verified the vision; verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,106,This is surely an obvious trial
  37,107,And we ransomed him with a mighty victim
  37,108,and we left for him amongst posterity
  37,109,Peace upon Abraham
  37,110,thus do we reward those who do well
  37,111,"verily, he was of our servants who believe"
  37,112,"And we gave him glad tidings of Isaac, a prophet among the righteous"
  37,113,"and we blessed him and Isaac;- of their seed is one who does well, and one who obviously wrongs himself"
  37,114,And we were gracious unto Moses and Aaron
  37,115,We saved them and their people from mighty trouble
  37,116,and we helped them and they had the upper hand
  37,117,and we gave them both the perspicuous Book
  37,118,and we guided them to the right way
  37,119,and we left for them amongst posterity
  37,120,Peace upon Moses and Aaron
  37,121,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,122,"verily, they were both of our servants who believe"
  37,123,And verily Elyas was of the apostles
  37,124,"when he said to his people, 'Will ye not fear"
  37,125,do ye call upon Baal and leave the best of Creators
  37,126,God your Lord and the Lord of your fathers of yore
  37,127,"But they called him liar; verily, they shall surely be arraigned"
  37,128,save God's sincere servants
  37,129,"And we, left for him amongst posterity"
  37,130,Peace upon Elyasin
  37,131,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,132,"verily, he was of our servants who believe"
  37,133,"And, verily, Lot was surely among the apostles"
  37,134,when we saved him and his people altogether
  37,135,except an old woman amongst those who lingered
  37,136,then we destroyed the others
  37,137,"verily, ye pass by them in the morning"
  37,138,and at night; have ye then no sense
  37,139,"And, verily, Jonah was amongst the apostles"
  37,140,when he ran away into the laden ship
  37,141,and he cast lots and was of those who lost
  37,142,"and a fish swallowed him, for he was to be blamed"
  37,143,and had it not been that he was of those who celebrated God's praises
  37,144,he would surely have tarried in the belly thereof to the day when men shall be raised
  37,145,But we cast him on to the barren shore; and he was sick
  37,146,and we made to grow over him a gourd tree
  37,147,and we sent him to a hundred thousand or more
  37,148,and they believed; and we gave them enjoyment for a season
  37,149,"Ask them, 'Has thy Lord daughters while they have sons"
  37,150,or have we created the angels females while they were witnesses
  37,151,is it not of their lie that they say
  37,152,"God has begotten?' verily, they are liars"
  37,153,Has he preferred daughters to sons
  37,154,what ails you? how ye judge
  37,155,will ye not be mindful
  37,156,or have ye obvious authority
  37,157,then bring your Book if ye do speak the truth
  37,158,"And they made him to be related to the ginns, while the ginns know that they shall be arraigned"
  37,159,celebrated be God's praises from what they attribute
  37,160,save God's sincere servants
  37,161,"Verily, ye and what ye worship"
  37,162,shall not try any one concerning him
  37,163,save him who shall broil in hell
  37,164,"there is none amongst us but has his appointed place, and"
  37,165,"verily, we are ranged, and"
  37,166,"verily, we celebrate His praises"
  37,167,And yet they say
  37,168,Had we a reminder from those of yore
  37,169,we should surely have been of God's sincere servants
  37,170,But they misbelieved in it; but soon shall they know
  37,171,But our word has been passed to our servants who were sent
  37,172,that they should be helped
  37,173,"that, verily, our hosts should gain mastery for them"
  37,174,Then turn thou thy back upon them for a time
  37,175,"and look upon them, for soon they too shall look"
  37,176,Would they hasten on our torment
  37,177,"but when it descends in their court, ill will the morning be of those who have been warned"
  37,178,But turn thy back upon them for a time
  37,179,"and look, for soon they too shall look"
  37,180,"Celebrated be the praises of thy Lord, the Lord of glory, above what they attribute"
  37,181,and peace be upon the apostles
  37,182,"and praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  38,1,By the Qur'an with its reminder
  38,2,"nay, but those who misbelieve are in pride, schism"
  38,3,"How many a generation have we destroyed before them, and they cried out, but it was no time to escape"
  38,4,"And they wonder that a warner has come from amongst themselves, and the misbelievers say, 'This is a magician, a liar"
  38,5,"What! does he make the gods to be one God? verily, this is a wondrous thing"
  38,6,"And the chiefs of them went away: 'Go on and persevere in your gods; this is a thing designed"
  38,7,we never heard this in any other sect; this is nothing but a fiction
  38,8,"Has a reminder come down upon him from amongst us?' nay, they are in doubt concerning my reminder; nay, they have not yet tasted of my torment"
  38,9,"Have they the treasures of the mercy of thy mighty Lord, the giver"
  38,10,"or have they the kingdom of the heavens and of the earth, and what is between the two?- then let them climb tip the ropes thereof"
  38,11,Any host whatever of the confederates shall there be routed
  38,12,"Before them did Noah's people, and 'Ad, and Pharaoh of the stakes call the apostles liars"
  38,13,"and Thamud and the people of Lot, and the fellows of the Grove, they were the confederates too"
  38,14,"They all did naught but call the apostles liars, and just was the punishment"
  38,15,Do these await aught else but one noise for which there shall be no pause
  38,16,"But they say, 'O our Lord, hasten for us our share before the day of reckoning"
  38,17,"Be patient of what they say, and remember our servant David endowed with might; verily, he turned frequently to us"
  38,18,"Verily, we subjected the mountains to celebrate with him our praises at the evening and the dawn"
  38,19,"and the birds too gathered together, each one would oft return to him"
  38,20,"and we strengthened his kingdom, and we gave him wisdom and decisive address"
  38,21,Has there come to thee the story of the antagonists when they scaled the chamber wall
  38,22,"when they entered in unto David, and he was startled at them, they said, 'Fear not, we are two antagonists; one of us has injured the other; judge then between us with the truth and be not partial, but guide us to a level way"
  38,23,"Verily, this is my brother: be had ninety-nine ewes and I had one ewe; and he said, \"Give her over to my charge;\" and he overcame me in the discourse"
  38,24,"Said he, 'He wronged thee in asking for thy ewe in addition to his own ewes. Verily, many associates do injure one another, except those who believe and do what is right, and very few are they!' And he thought that we were trying him; and he asked pardon of his Lord and fell down bowing, and did turn"
  38,25,"and we pardoned him; for, verily, he has a near approach to us and an excellent resort"
  38,26,"O David! verily, we have made thee a vicegerent, judge then between men with truth and follow not lust, for it will lead thee astray from the path of god. Verily, those who go astray from the path of God, for them is keen torment, for that they did forget the day of reckoning"
  38,27,"And we have not created the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two, in vain. That is what those who misbelieved did think, but woe from the fire to those who misbelieve"
  38,28,Shall we make those who believe and do right like those who do evil in the earth? or shall we make the pious like the sinners
  38,29,"A blessed Book which we have sent down to thee that they may consider its verses, and that those endowed with minds may be mindful"
  38,30,"And we gave to David, Solomon, an excellent servant; verily, he turned frequently to us"
  38,31,When there were set before him in the evening the steeds that paw the ground
  38,32,"and he said, 'Verily, I have loved the love of good things better than the remembrance of my Lord, until (the sun) was hidden behind the veil"
  38,33,bring them back to me;' and he began to sever their legs and necks
  38,34,"And we did try Solomon, and we threw upon his throne a form; then he turned repentant"
  38,35,"Said he, 'My Lord, pardon me and grant me a kingdom that is not seemly for any one after me; verily, thou art He who grants"
  38,36,And we subjected to him the wind to run on at his bidding gently wherever he directed it
  38,37,and the devils - every builder and diver
  38,38,and others bound in fetters
  38,39,"this is our gift, so be thou lavish or withhold without account"
  38,40,"And, verily, he had with us a near approach, and a good resort"
  38,41,And remember our servant Job when he called upon his Lord that 'the devil has touched me with toil and torment
  38,42,"Stamp with thy foot, this is a cool washing-place and a drink"
  38,43,"And we granted him his family, and the like of them with them, as a mercy from us and a reminder to those endowed with minds"
  38,44,"and take in thy hand a bundle, and strike therewith, and break not thy oath!' Verily, we found him patient, an excellent servant; verily, he turned frequently to us"
  38,45,"And remember our servants Abraham and Isaac and Jacob, endowed with might and sight"
  38,46,"verily, we made them sincere by a sincere quality - the remembrance of the abode"
  38,47,"and, verily, they were with us of the elect, the best"
  38,48,"And remember Ishmael and Elisha and Dhu-l-kifl, for each was of the righteous"
  38,49,"This is a reminder! verily, for the pious is there an excellent resort"
  38,50,gardens of Eden with the doors open to them
  38,51,reclining therein; calling therein for much fruit and drink
  38,52,"and beside them maids of modest glance, of their own age"
  38,53,This is what ye were promised for the day of reckoning
  38,54,"This is surely our provision, it is never spent"
  38,55,"This!- and, verily, for the rebellious is there an evil resort"
  38,56,"hell; they shall broil therein, and an ill couch shall it be"
  38,57,"This,- so let them taste it!- hot water, and pus"
  38,58,and other kinds of the same sort
  38,59,"This is an army plunged in with you! there is no welcome for them! verily, they are going to broil in the fire"
  38,60,"They shall say, 'Nay, for you too is there no welcome! it was ye who prepared it beforehand for us, and an ill resting-place it is"
  38,61,"They shall say, 'Our Lord! whoso prepared this beforehand for us, give him double torment in the fire"
  38,62,"And they shall say, 'What ails us that we do not see men whom we used to think amongst the wicked"
  38,63,whom we used to take for mockery? have our eyes escaped them
  38,64,"Verily, that is the truth; the contention of the people of the fire"
  38,65,"Say, 'I am only a warner; and there is no god but God, the one, the victorious"
  38,66,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two, the mighty, the forgiving"
  38,67,"Say, 'It is a grand story"
  38,68,and yet ye turn from it
  38,69,I had no knowledge of the exalted chiefs when they contended
  38,70,I am only inspired that I am a plain warner
  38,71,"When thy Lord said to the angels, 'Verily, I am about to create a mortal out of clay"
  38,72,"and when I have fashioned him, and breathed into him of my spirit, then fall ye down before him adoring"
  38,73,And the angels adored all of them
  38,74,"save Iblis, who was too big with pride, and was of the misbelievers"
  38,75,"Said He, 'O Iblis! what prevents thee from adoring what I have created with my two hands? art thou too big with pride? or art thou amongst the exalted"
  38,76,"Said he, 'I am better than he, Thou hast created me from fire, and him Thou hast created from clay"
  38,77,"Said He, 'Then go forth therefrom, for, Verily, thou art pelted"
  38,78,"and, verily, upon thee is my curse unto the day of judgment"
  38,79,"Said be, 'My Lord! then respite me until the day when they are raised"
  38,80,"Said He, 'Then thou art amongst the respited"
  38,81,until the day of the stated time
  38,82,"Said he, 'Then, by Thy might! I will surely seduce them all together"
  38,83,except Thy servants amongst them who are sincere
  38,84,"Said He, 'It is the truth, and the truth I speak"
  38,85,I will surely fill hell with thee and with those who follow thee amongst them all together
  38,86,"Say, 'I do not ask thee for it any hire, nor am I of those who take too much upon myself"
  38,87,It is but a reminder to the servants
  38,88,and ye shall surely know its story after a time
  39,1,"The sending down of the Book from God, the mighty, the wise"
  39,2,"Verily, we have sent down to thee the Book in truth, then serve God, being sincere in religion unto Him"
  39,3,"Aye! God's is the sincere religion: and those who take beside Him patrons - 'We do not serve them save that they may bring us near to God - 'Verily, God will judge between them concerning that whereon they do dispute. Verily, God guides not him who is a misbelieving liar"
  39,4,"Had God wished to take to Himself a child, He would have chosen what He pleased from what He creates;- celebrated be His praises! He is God, the one, the victorious"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth in truth! It is He who clothes the day with night; and clothes the night with day; and subjects the sun and the moon, each one runs on to an appointed time; aye! He is the mighty, the forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you from one soul; then He made from it its mate; and He sent down upon you of the cattle four pairs! He creates you in the bellies of your mothers,- creation after creation, in three darknesses. That is God for you! His is the kingdom, there is no god but He; how then can ye be turned away"
  39,7,"If ye be thankless, yet is God independent of you. He is not pleased with ingratitude in His servants; but if ye give thanks, He is pleased with that in you. But no burdened soul shall bear the burden of another; then unto your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of that which ye have done. Verily, He knows the natures of men's breasts"
  39,8,"And when distress touches a man he calls his Lord, turning repentant to Him; then when He confers on him a favour from Himself he forgets what he had called upon Him for before, and makes peers for God to lead astray from His way! Say, 'Enjoy thyself in thy misbelief a little, verily, thou art of the fellows of the Fire"
  39,9,"Shall he who is devout throughout the night, adoring and standing, cautious concerning the hereafter, and hoping for the mercy of his Lord . . . ? Say, 'Shall those who know be deemed equal with those who know not? only those will remember, who are endowed with minds"
  39,10,"Say, 'O my servants who believe! fear your Lord! for those who do well in this world is good, and God's earth is spacious; verily, the patient shall be paid their hire without count"
  39,11,"Say, 'Verily, I am bidden to serve God, being sincere in religion to Him"
  39,12,and I am bidden that I be the first of those resigned
  39,13,"Say, 'Verily, I fear, if I rebel against my Lord, the torment of a mighty day"
  39,14,"Say, 'God do I serve, being sincere in my relation to Him"
  39,15,"serve then what ye will beside Him!' Say, 'Verily, the losers are those who lose themselves and their families on the resurrection day. Aye, that is the obvious loss"
  39,16,"They shall have over them shades of fire, and under them shades; with that does God frighten His servants: O my servants! then fear me"
  39,17,"But those who avoid Taghut and serve them not, but turn repentant unto God, for them shall be glad tidings. Then give glad tidings to my servants"
  39,18,"who listen to the word and follow the best thereof; they it is whom God guides, and they it is who are endowed with minds"
  39,19,"Him against whom the word of torment is due,- canst thou rescue him from the fire"
  39,20,"But for those who fear their Lord for them are upper chambers, and upper chambers above them built, beneath which rivers flow; God's promise! God does not fail in His promise"
  39,21,"Hast thou not seen that God sends down from the heaven water, and conducts it into springs in the earth? then He brings forth therewith corn varied in kind, then it dries up, and ye see it grow yellow; then He makes it grit;- verily, in that is a reminder for those endowed with minds"
  39,22,"Is he whose breast God has expanded for Islam, and who is in light from his Lord .... ? And woe to those whose hearts are hardened against a remembrance of God! those are in obvious error"
  39,23,"God has sent down the best of legends, a book uniform and repeating; whereat the skins of those who fear their Lord do creep! then their skins and their hearts soften at the remembrance of God. That is the guidance of God! He guides therewith whom He will. But he whom God leads astray there is no guide for him"
  39,24,"Shall he who must screen himself with his own face from the evil torment on the resurrection day. . . . ? And it shall be said of those who do wrong, taste what ye have earned"
  39,25,"Those before them called the (prophets) liars, and the torment came to them from whence they perceived it not"
  39,26,"and God made them taste disgrace in the life of this world. But surely the torment of the hereafter is greater, if they did but know"
  39,27,"We have struck out for men in this Qur'an every sort of parable, haply they may be mindful"
  39,28,An Arabic Qur'an with no crookedness therein; haply they may fear
  39,29,"God has struck out a parable, a man who has partners who oppose each other and a man who is wholly given up to another; shall they be deemed equal in similitude? praise be to God! nay, but most of them know not"
  39,30,"Verily, thou shalt die, and, verily, they shall die"
  39,31,"then, verily, on the resurrection day before your Lord shall ye dispute"
  39,32,"And who is more unjust than he who lies against God, and calls the truth a lie when it comes to him? Is there not in hell a resort for those who misbelieve"
  39,33,"but whoso brings the truth and believes in it, these are they who fear"
  39,34,"For them is what they please with their Lord, that is the reward of those who do well"
  39,35,"that God may cover for them their offences which they have done, and may reward them with their hire for the best of that which they have done"
  39,36,Is not God sufficient for His servants? and yet they would frighten thee with those beside Him
  39,37,"But he whom God leads astray there is no guide for him; and he whom God guides there is none to lead him astray: is not God mighty, the Lord of vengeance"
  39,38,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, 'God!' Say, 'Have ye considered what ye call on beside God? If God wished me harm, could they remove His harm? or did He wish me mercy, could they withhold His mercy?' Say, 'God is enough for me, and on Him rely those who rely"
  39,39,"Say, 'O my people! act according to your power; I too am going to act; and ye shall know"
  39,40,"He to whom the torment comes it shall disgrace him, and there shall alight upon him lasting torment"
  39,41,"Verily, we have sent down to thee the Book for men in truth; and whosoever is guided it is for his own soul: but whoso goes astray it is against them, and thou art not a guardian for them"
  39,42,"God takes to Himself souls at the time of their death; and those which do not die (He takes) in their sleep; and He holds back those on whom He has decreed death, and sends others back till their appointed time;- verily, in that are signs unto a people who reflect"
  39,43,"Do they take besides God intercessors? Say, 'What! though they have no control over anything and have no sense"
  39,44,"Say, 'God's is the intercession, all of it; His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; then unto Him shall ye be sent back"
  39,45,"And when God alone is mentioned the hearts of those who believe not in the hereafter quake, and when those beside Him are mentioned, lo, they are joyful"
  39,46,"Say, 'O God! originator of the heavens and the earth, who knowest the unseen and the visible, thou wilt judge between thy servants concerning that whereon they do dispute"
  39,47,"And had those who do wrong all that is in the earth, and the like thereof with it, they would ransom themselves therewith from the evil of the torment on the resurrection day! but there shall appear to them from God that which they had not reckoned on"
  39,48,and the evils of what they have earned shall appear to them; but that shall close in on them at which they mocked
  39,49,"And when harm touches man he calls on us; then, when we grant him favour from us, he says, 'Verily, I am given it through knowledge!' nay, it is a trial,- but most of them do not know"
  39,50,"Those before them said it too, but that availed them not which they had earned"
  39,51,"and there befell them the evil deeds of what they had earned: and those who do wrong of these (Meccans), there shall befall them too the evil deeds of what they had earned, nor shall they frustrate Him"
  39,52,"Have they not known that God extends His provision to whom He pleases, or doles it out? verily, in that are signs unto a people who believe"
  39,53,"Say, 'O my servants! who have been extravagant against their own souls!' be not in despair of the mercy of God; verily, God forgives sins, all of them; verily, He is forgiving, merciful"
  39,54,"But turn repentant unto your Lord, and resign yourselves to Him, before there comes on you torment! then ye shall not be helped"
  39,55,"and follow the best of what has been sent down to you from your Lord, before there come on you the torment suddenly, ere ye can perceive"
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say, 'O my sighing! for what I have neglected towards God! for, verily, I was amongst those who did jest"
  39,57,"or lest it should say, 'If God had but guided me, I should surely have been of those who fear"
  39,58,"or lest it should say, when it sees the torment, 'Had I another turn I should be of those who do well"
  39,59,"Yea! there came to thee my signs and thou didst call them lies, and wert too big with pride, and wert of those who misbelieved"
  39,60,"And on the resurrection day thou shalt see those who lied against God, with their faces blackened. Is there not in hell a resort for those who are too big with pride"
  39,61,"And God shall rescue those who fear Him, into their safe place; no evil shall touch them, nor shall they be grieved"
  39,62,"God is the creator of everything, and He is guardian over everything"
  39,63,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who misbelieve in the signs of God, they it is who lose"
  39,64,"Say, 'What! other than God would you bid me serve, O ye ignorant ones"
  39,65,"When He has inspired thee and those before thee that, \"If thou dost associate aught with Him, thy work will surely be in vain, and thou shalt surely be of those who lose"
  39,66,"Nay, but God do thou serve, and be of those who do give thanks"
  39,67,"And they do not value God at His true value; while the earth all of it is but a handful for Him on the resurrection day, and the heavens shall be rolled up in His right hand! Celebrated be His praise! and exalted be He above what they associate with Him"
  39,68,"And the trumpet shall be blown, and those who are in the heavens and in the earth shall swoon, save whom God pleases. Then it shall be blown again, and, lo! they shall stand up and look on"
  39,69,"And the earth shall beam with the light of its Lord, and the Book shall be set forth, and the prophets and martyrs shall be brought; and it shall be decreed between them in truth, and they shall not be wronged"
  39,70,"And every soul shall be paid for what it has done, and He knows best that which they do"
  39,71,"and those who misbelieve shall be driven to hell in troops; and when they come there, its doors shall be opened, and its keepers shall say to them, 'Did not apostles from amongst yourselves come to you to recite to you the signs of your Lord, and to warn you of the meeting of this day of yours?' They shall say, 'Yea, but the sentence of torment was due against the misbelievers"
  39,72,"It shall be said, 'Enter ye the gates of hell, to dwell therein for aye! Hell is the resort of those who are too big with pride"
  39,73,"But those who fear their Lord shall be driven to Paradise in troops; until they come there, its doors shall be opened, and its keepers shall say to them, 'Peace be upon you, ye have done well! so enter in to dwell for aye"
  39,74,"and they shall say, ' Praise be to God, who hath made good His promise to us, and hath given us the earth to inherit! We establish ourselves in Paradise wherever we please; and goodly is the reward of those who work"
  39,75,"And thou shalt see the angels circling round about the throne, celebrating the praise of their Lord; and it shall be decided between them in truth; and it shall be said, 'Praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,1,M
  40,2,"The sending down of the Book from God, the mighty, the knowing"
  40,3,"the forgiver of sin and accepter of repentance, keen at punishment, longsuffering! there is no god but He! to whom the journey is"
  40,4,None wrangle concerning the signs of God but those who misbelieve; then let not their going to and fro in the cities deceive thee
  40,5,"The people of Noah before them called the prophets liars; and the confederates after them; and every nation schemed against their Apostle to catch him. And they wrangled with falsehood that they might refute the truth thereby, but I seized them, and how was my punishment"
  40,6,"Thus was the sentence of thy Lord due against those who misbelieved, that they are the fellows of the Fire"
  40,7,"Those who bear the throne and those around it celebrate the praise of their Lord, and believe in Him, and ask pardon for those who believe: 'Our Lord! thou dost embrace all things in mercy and knowledge, then pardon those who turn repentant and follow thy way, and guard them from the torment of hell"
  40,8,"Our Lord! make them enter into gardens of Eden which thou hast promised to them, and to those who do well of their fathers, and their wives, and their seed; verily, thou art the mighty, the wise"
  40,9,"and guard them from evil deeds, for he whom thou shalt guard from evil deeds on that day, thou wilt have had mercy on, and that is mighty bliss"
  40,10,"Verily, those who misbelieve shall be cried out to, 'Surely, God's hatred is greater than your hatred of each other when ye were called unto the faith and misbelieved"
  40,11,"They shall say, 'Our Lord! Thou hast killed us twice, and Thou hast quickened us twice; and we do confess our sins: is there then a way for getting out"
  40,12,"That is because when God alone was proclaimed ye did disbelieve; but when partners were joined to Him ye did believe; but judgment belongs to God, the high, the great"
  40,13,"He it is who shows you His signs, and sends down to you from heaven provision; but none is mindful except him who turns repentant"
  40,14,"then call on God, being sincere in your religion to Him, averse although the misbelievers be"
  40,15,"Exalted of degrees! The Lord of the throne! He throws the spirit by His bidding upon whom He will of His servants, to give warning of the day of meeting"
  40,16,"The day when they shall be issuing forth, naught concerning them shall be hidden from God. Whose is the kingdom on that day?- God's, the one, the dominant"
  40,17,"today shall every soul be recompensed for that which it has earned. There is no wrong today; verily, God is quick at reckoning up"
  40,18,"And warn them of the day that approaches, when hearts are choking in the gullets; those who do wrong shall have no warm friend, and no intercessor who shall be obeyed"
  40,19,He knows the deceitful of eye and what men's breasts conceal
  40,20,"and God decides with truth; but those they call on beside Him do not decide at all: verily, God, He both hears and looks"
  40,21,"Have, they not journeyed on in the earth and seen how was the end of those who journeyed on before them? They were stronger than them in might, and their vestiges are in the land, but God caught them up in their sins, and they had none to guard them against God"
  40,22,"That is for that their apostles did come to them with manifest signs, and they misbelieved, and God caught them up; verily, He is mighty, keen to punish"
  40,23,"And we did send Moses with our signs, and with obvious authority"
  40,24,"unto Pharaoh and Haman and Qarun. They said, 'A lying sorcerer"
  40,25,"and when they came to them with truth from us, they said, 'Kill the sons of those who believe with him, and let their women live!' but the stratagem of the misbelievers is only in error"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, 'Let me kill Moses; and then let him call upon his Lord! verily, I fear that he will change your religion, or that he will cause evil doing to appear in the land"
  40,27,"And Moses said, 'Verily, I take refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every one who is big with pride and believes not on the day of reckoning"
  40,28,"And a believing man of Pharaoh's people, who concealed his faith, said, 'Will ye kill a man for saying, My Lord is God, when he has come to you with manifest signs from your Lord? and if he be a liar, against him is his lie; and if he be truthful, there will befall you somewhat of that which he threatens you; verily, God guides not him who is an extravagant liar"
  40,29,"O my people! yours is the kingdom today, ye are eminent in the land, but who will help us against the violence of God, if it comes upon us?' Said Pharaoh, 'I will only show you what I see, and I will only guide you into the way of right direction"
  40,30,"And he who believed said, 'O my people! verily, I fear for you the like of the day of the confederates"
  40,31,"the like of the wont of the people of Noah and 'Ad and Haman, and of those after them; for God desires not injustice for His servants"
  40,32,"O my people! verily, I fear for you the day of crying out"
  40,33,"the day when ye shall turn your backs, fleeing, with no defender for you against God; for he whom God leads astray, for him there is no guide"
  40,34,"And Joseph came to you before with manifest signs, but ye ceased not to doubt concerning what he brought you, until, when he perished, ye said, \"God will not send after him an apostle;\" thus does God lead astray him who is extravagant, a doubter"
  40,35,Those who wrangle concerning the signs of God without authority having come to them are greatly hated by God and by those who believe; thus does God set a stamp upon the heart of every tyrant too big with pride
  40,36,"And Pharaoh said, 'O Haman! build for me a tower, haply I may reach the tracts"
  40,37,"the tracts of heaven, and may mount up to the God of Moses, for, verily, I think him a liar.' And thus was his evil deed made seemly to Pharaoh, and he was turned from the way; but Pharaoh's stratagem ended only in ruin"
  40,38,"and he who believed said, 'O my people! follow me, I will guide you to the way of the right direction"
  40,39,"O my people! verily, the life of this world is but a provision, but, verily, the hereafter, that is the abode of stability"
  40,40,"Whoso does evil, he shall only be recompensed with the like thereof , and whoso does right, be it male or female and a believer, these shall enter into Paradise; they shall be provided therein without count"
  40,41,"O my people! why should I call you to salvation, and you call me to the fire"
  40,42,"Ye call on me to disbelieve in God, and to join with Him what I have no knowledge of; but I call you to the mighty forgiving One"
  40,43,"no doubt that what ye call me to, ought not to be called on in this world or in the hereafter, and that we shall be sent back to God, and that the extravagant, they are the fellows of the Fire"
  40,44,"But ye shall remember what I say to you; and I entrust my affair to God, verily, God looks upon His servants"
  40,45,"And God guarded him from the evils of what they plotted, and there closed in upon Pharaoh evil woe"
  40,46,"The fire - they shall be exposed to it morning and evening; and 'on the day the Hour shall arise,' enter, O people of Pharaoh! into the keenest torment"
  40,47,"And when they argue together in the fire, and the weak say to those who were big with pride, 'Verily, we were followers of yours, can ye then avail us against a portion of the fire"
  40,48,"Those who were big with pride shall say, 'Verily, we are all in it; verily, God has judged between His servants"
  40,49,"And those who are in the fire shall say unto the keepers of hell, 'Call upon your Lord to lighten from us one day of the torment"
  40,50,"They shall say, 'Did not your apostles come to you with manifest signs?' They shall say, 'Yea!' They shall say, 'Then call!- but the call of the misbelievers is only in error"
  40,51,"Verily, we will help our apostles, and those who believe, in the life of this world and on the day when the witnesses shall stand up"
  40,52,"the day when their excuse shall not avail the unjust; but for them is the curse, and for them is an evil abode"
  40,53,And we did give Moses the guidance; and we made the children of Israel to inherit the Book
  40,54,as a guidance and a reminder to those endowed with minds
  40,55,"Be thou patient, then; verily, God's promise is true: and ask thou forgiveness for thy sins, and celebrate the praise of thy Lord in the evening and in the morn"
  40,56,"Verily, those who wrangle concerning the signs of God without authority having come to them, there is naught in their breasts but pride; but they shall not attain it: do thou then seek refuge in God; verily, He both hears and looks"
  40,57,"Surely the creation of the heavens and the earth is greater than the creation of man: but most men know it not"
  40,58,"The blind and the seeing shall not be deemed alike, nor those who believe and do right and the evildoer; little is it that they remember"
  40,59,"Verily, the Hour will surely come; there is no doubt therein; but most men do not believe"
  40,60,"And your Lord said, 'Call upon me, I will answer you; verily, those who are too big with pride to worship shall enter into hell, shrinking up"
  40,61,"God it is who has made for you the night to repose therein, and the day to see by; verily, God is Lord of grace to men, but most men give no thanks"
  40,62,"There is God for you! your Lord the creator of everything! there is no god but He, how then can ye lie"
  40,63,Thus did those lie who gainsaid the signs of God
  40,64,"God it is who has made for you the earth as a resting-place, and a heaven as building, and has formed you and made excellent your forms; and has provided you with good things! there is God for you!- your Lord! then blessed be God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,65,"He is the living One, there is no god but He! then call on Him, being sincere in your religion to Him; praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,66,"Say, 'Verily, I am forbidden to serve those whom ye call on beside God, since there have come to me manifest signs from my Lord, and I am bidden to be resigned unto the Lord of the worlds"
  40,67,"He it is who created you from the earth, then from a clot, then from congealed blood, then He brings you forth a child; then ye reach to puberty; then do ye become old men,- though of you there are some who are taken away before,- that ye may reach an appointed time, and haply ye may have some sense"
  40,68,"He it is who quickens and kills, and when He decrees a matter, then He only says to it, 'BE,' and it is"
  40,69,Hast thou not seen those who wrangle concerning the signs of God how they are turned away
  40,70,"Those who call the Book, and what we have sent our apostles with, a lie, soon shall they know"
  40,71,"when the fetters are on their necks and the chains, as they are dragged"
  40,72,into hell!- then in the fire shall they be baked
  40,73,"Then it shall be said to them, 'Where is what ye did associate"
  40,74,"beside God?' They shall say, 'They have strayed away from us; nay, we did not call before upon anything!' - thus does God lead the misbelievers astray"
  40,75,There! for 'that ye did rejoice in the land without right; and for that ye did exult
  40,76,"enter ye the gates of hell, to dwell therein for aye; for evil is the resort of those who are too big with pride"
  40,77,"But be thou patient; verily, the promise of God is true; and whether we show thee a part of what we promised them, or whether we surely take thee to ourself, unto us shall they be returned"
  40,78,"And we did send apostles before thee: of them are some whose stories we have related to thee, and of them are some whose stories we have not related to thee; and no apostle might ever bring a sign except by the permission of God; but when God's bidding came it was decided with truth, and there were those lost who deemed it vain"
  40,79,"God it is who has made for you cattle, that ye may ride on some of them;- and of them ye eat"
  40,80,and ye have in them advantages;- and that ye may attain thereon a want which is in your breasts; upon them and upon ships are ye borne
  40,81,He shows you His signs; which sign then of your Lord do ye deny
  40,82,"Have they not journeyed on in the land and seen how was the end of those before them, who were more numerous than they and stronger in might, and in their vestiges which are still in the land? but of no avail to them was that which they had earned"
  40,83,And when there came to them their apostles with manifest signs they rejoiced in what knowledge they had; but there closed in upon them that whereat they had mocked
  40,84,"And when they saw our violence they said, 'We believe in God alone, and we disbelieve in what we once associated with Him"
  40,85,"But their faith was of no avail to them when they saw our violence - the course of God with His servants in time past, and there the misbelievers lose"
  41,1,M
  41,2,"A revelation from the merciful, the compassionate"
  41,3,a book whose signs are detailed; an Arabic Qur'an for a people who do know
  41,4,a herald of glad tidings and a warning. But most of them turn aside and do not hear
  41,5,"and say, 'Our hearts are veiled from what thou dost call us to, and in our ears is dullness, and between us and thee there is a veil. Act thou; verily, we are acting too"
  41,6,"Say, 'I am but a mortal like yourselves, I am inspired that your God is one God; then go straight to Him, and ask forgiveness of Him; and woe to the idolaters"
  41,7,"who give not alms, and in the hereafter disbelieve"
  41,8,"Verily, those who believe and do right, for them is a hire that is not grudged"
  41,9,"Say, 'What! do ye really misbelieve in Him who created the earth in two days, and do ye make peers for Him?- that is the Lord of the worlds"
  41,10,"And He placed thereon firm mountains above it and blessed it, and apportioned therein its foods in four days alike for those who ask"
  41,11,"Then He made for the heaven and it was but smoke, and He said to it and to the earth, 'Come, ye two, whether ye will or no!' They said, 'We come willingly"
  41,12,"And He decreed them seven heavens in two days, and inspired every heaven with its bidding: and we adorned the lower heaven with lamps and guardian angels; that is the decree of the mighty, the knowing One"
  41,13,"But if they turn aside, then say, 'I have warned you of a thunder-clap like the thunder-clap of 'Ad and Thamud"
  41,14,"when their apostles came to them from before them and from behind them (saying), \"Serve ye none but God.\"' They said, 'If our Lord pleased He would send down angels; so we in what ye are sent with disbelieve"
  41,15,"And as for 'Ad, they were big with pride in the land, without right, and said, 'Who is stronger than us in might?' Did they not see that God who created them He was stronger than they in might? But they did gainsay our signs"
  41,16,"And we sent upon them a cold blast in unfortunate days, that we might make them taste the torment of disgrace in the life of this world;- but the torment of the hereafter is more disgraceful, and they shall not be helped"
  41,17,"And as for Thamud we guided them; but they preferred blindness to guidance, and the thunder-clap of the torment of abasement caught them for what they had earned"
  41,18,but we saved those who believed and who did fear
  41,19,"And the day when the enemies of God shall be gathered together into the fire, marshalled along"
  41,20,"until when they come to it, their hearing and their eyesight and their skins shall bear witness against them of that which they have done"
  41,21,"And they shall say to their skins, 'Why have ye borne witness against us?' they shall say, 'God gave us speech who has given speech to everything; He created you at first, and unto Him shall ye be returned"
  41,22,"and ye could not conceal yourselves that your hearing and your eyesight should not be witness against you, nor your skins; but ye thought that God did not know much of what ye do"
  41,23,"And that thought of yours which ye thought concerning your Lord has destroyed you, and ye have now become of those who lose"
  41,24,"And if they are patient, still the fire is a resort for them; and if they ask for favour again, they shall not be taken into favour"
  41,25,"We will allot to them mates, for they have made seemly to them what was before them and what was behind them; and due against them was the sentence on the nations who passed away before them; both of ginns and of mankind; verily, they were the losers"
  41,26,"Those who misbelieve say, 'Listen not to this Qur'an, but talk foolishly about it, haply ye may gain the upper hand"
  41,27,But we will make those who misbelieve taste keen torment; and we will recompense them with the worst of that which they have done
  41,28,"That is, the recompense of the enemies of God,- the fire! for them is an eternal abode therein: a recompense for that they did gainsay our signs"
  41,29,"And those who misbelieved say, 'Our Lord, show us those who have led us astray amongst the ginns and mankind; we will place them beneath our feet, and they shall both be amongst those who are put down"
  41,30,"Verily, those who say, 'Our Lord is God,' and then go straight, the angels descend upon them - 'fear not and be not grieved, but receive the glad tidings of Paradise which ye were promised"
  41,31,"we are your patrons in the life of this world and in the next, and ye shall have therein what your souls desire, and ye shall have therein what ye call for"
  41,32,"an entertainment from the forgiving, the merciful"
  41,33,"And who speaks better than he who calls to God and does right, and says, 'Verily, I am of those resigned"
  41,34,"Good and evil shall not be deemed alike; repel (evil) with what is best, and lo! He between whom and thyself was enmity is as though he were a warm patron"
  41,35,But none shall meet with it save those who are patient; and none shall meet with it save those who are endowed with mighty good fortune
  41,36,"And if an incitement from the devil incites you, then seek refuge in God; verily, He both hears and knows"
  41,37,"And of His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. Adore ye not the sun, neither the moon; but adore God who created you, if it be Him ye serve"
  41,38,"But if they be too big with pride - yet those who are with thy Lord celebrate His praises by night and day, and they are never weary"
  41,39,"And of His signs (is this), that thou mayest see the earth drooping, and when we send down water upon it it stirs and swells; verily, He who quickens it will surely quicken the dead; verily, He is mighty over all"
  41,40,"Verily, those who are inclined to oppose our signs are not hidden from us. Is he who is cast into the fire better, or he who comes safe on the resurrection day? Do what ye will: verily, He on what ye do doth look"
  41,41,"Verily, those who misbelieve in the reminder when it comes to them - and, verily, it is a glorious Book"
  41,42,"falsehood shall not come to it, from before it, nor from behind it - a revelation from the wise, the praiseworthy One"
  41,43,"Naught is said to thee but what was said to the apostles before thee, 'Verily, thy Lord is Lord of forgiveness and Lord of grievous torment"
  41,44,"And had we made it a foreign Qur'an, they would have said, 'Unless its signs be detailed. .. . What! foreign and Arabic?' Say, 'It is, for those who believe, a guidance and a healing. But those who believe not, in their ears is dullness, and it is blindness to them; these are called to from a far-off place"
  41,45,"And we gave Moses the Book, and it was disputed about; but had it not been for thy Lord's word already passed it would have been decided between them, for, verily, they were in hesitating doubt thereon"
  41,46,"Whoso does right it is for his soul, and whoso does evil it is against it, for thy Lord is not unjust towards His servants"
  41,47,"To Him is referred the knowledge of the Hour: and no fruits come forth from their husks, and no female conceives, or is delivered, save with His knowledge. And the day when He shall call to them, 'Where are the partners ye did join with me"
  41,48,"they shall say, 'We do own to thee there is no witness amongst us!' and that on which they used to call before shall stray away from them, and they shall think there is no escape for them"
  41,49,"Man is never tired of praying for good, but if evil touch him, then he is despairing and hopeless"
  41,50,"But if we make him taste mercy from us after distress has touched him he will surely say, 'This is for me, and I do not think the Hour is imminent; and if I be brought back to my Lord, verily, I shall surely have good with Him;' but we will inform those who misbelieve of what they have done, and we will surely make them taste wretched torment"
  41,51,"And when we have been gracious to man, he turns away and goes aside; but when evil touches him he is one of copious prayer"
  41,52,"Say, 'Let us see now! if it be from God and ye disbelieve in it, who is more in error than he who is in a remote schism"
  41,53,"We will show them our signs in the regions and in themselves, until it is plain to them that it is the truth. Is it not enough for thy Lord that He is witness over all"
  41,54,"Ay, verily, they are in doubt about the meeting of their Lord! Ay, verily, He encompasses all"
  42,1,M
  42,2,Q
  42,3,"Thus does God, the mighty, the wise, inspire thee and those before thee"
  42,4,"His is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth, and He is the high, the mighty"
  42,5,"The heavens well-nigh cleave asunder from above them; and the angels celebrate the praises of their Lord, and ask forgiveness for those who are on the earth. Ay, verily, God, He is the forgiving and merciful"
  42,6,"but those who take beside Him patrons, God watches over them, and thou hast not charge over them"
  42,7,"Thus have we revealed an Arabic Qur'an, that thou mayest warn the Mother of cities and all around it; and warn them of a day of gathering, there is no doubt therein;- a part in Paradise and a part in the blaze"
  42,8,But had God pleased He would have made them one nation; but He makes whom He will enter into His mercy; and the unjust have neither patron nor help
  42,9,"Do they take other patrons besides Him, when God He is the patron, and He quickens the dead and He is mighty over all"
  42,10,"But whatsoever ye dispute about, the judgment of it is God's. There is God for you!- my Lord! upon Him do I rely, and unto Him I turn repentant"
  42,11,"The originator of the heavens and the earth, He has made for you from yourselves wives; and of the cattle mates; producing you thereby. There is naught like Him, for He both hears and sees"
  42,12,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth, He extends provision to whom He will, or doles it out; verily, He knows everything"
  42,13,"He has enjoined upon you for religion what He prescribed to Noah and what we inspired thee with, and what we inspired Abraham and Moses and Jesus,- to be steadfast in religion, and not to part into sects therein - a great thing to the idolaters is that which ye call them to! God elects for Himself whom He pleases and guides unto Himself him who turns repentant"
  42,14,"But they did not part into sects until after the knowledge had come to them, through mutual envy; and had it not been for thy Lord's word already passed for an appointed time, it would surely have been decided between them; but, verily, those who have been given the Book as an inheritance after them, are in hesitating doubt concerning it"
  42,15,"Wherefore call thou, and go straight on as thou art bidden, and follow not their lusts; and say, 'I believe in the Book which God has sent down; and I am bidden to judge justly between you. God is our Lord and your Lord; we have our works and ye have your works; there is no argument between us and you. God will assemble us together and unto Him the journey is"
  42,16,"But those who argue about God after it has been assented to, their arguments shall be rebutted before their Lord; and upon them shall be wrath, and for them shall be keen torment"
  42,17,"God it is who has sent down the Book with truth, and the balance; and what shall make thee know whether haply the Hour be nigh"
  42,18,"Those who believe not would hurry it on; and those who believe shrink with terror at it and know that it is true. Ay, verily, those who dispute concerning the Hour are in remote error"
  42,19,"God is kind to His servants; He Provides whom He will, and He is the mighty, the glorious"
  42,20,"He who wishes for the tilth of the next world, we will increase for him the tilth; and he who desires the tilth of this world, we will give him thereof: but in the next he shall have no portion"
  42,21,"Have they associates who have enjoined any religion on them which God permits not?- but were it not for the word of decision it would have been decreed to them. Verily, the unjust,- for them is grievous woe"
  42,22,"Thou shalt see the unjust shrink with terror from what they have gained as it falls upon them; and those who believe and do right, in meads of Paradise, they shall have what they please with their Lord;- that is great grace"
  42,23,"That is what God gives glad tidings of to His servants who believe and do righteous acts. Say, 'I do not ask for it a hire - only the love of my kinsfolk.' And he who gains a good action we will increase good for him thereby; verily, God is forgiving and grateful"
  42,24,"Or will they say he has forged against God a lie? But if God pleased He could set a seal upon thy heart; but God will blot out falsehood and verify truth by His word; verily, He knows the nature of men's breasts"
  42,25,He it is who accepts repentance from His servants and pardons their offences and knows that which ye do
  42,26,"And He answers the prayer of those who believe and do right, and gives them increase of His grace; but the misbelievers,- for them is keen torment"
  42,27,"And if God were to extend provision to His servants they would be wanton in the earth. But He sends down by measure what He pleases; verily, of His servants He is well aware and sees"
  42,28,"He it is who sends down the rain after they have despaired; and disperses His mercy, for He is the praiseworthy patron"
  42,29,"And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and what He hath spread abroad therein of beasts; and He is able to collect them when He will"
  42,30,And what misfortunes befall you it is for what your hands have earned; but He pardons much
  42,31,"yet ye cannot make Him helpless in the earth, nor have ye, besides God, either a patron or a helper"
  42,32,And of His signs are the ships that sail like mountains in the sea
  42,33,"If He will, He calms the wind, and they become motionless on the back thereof: verily, in that are signs to every patient, grateful person"
  42,34,or He makes them founder for what they have earned; but He pardons much
  42,35,But let those who wrangle about our signs know that they shall have no escape
  42,36,And whatever ye are given it is but a provision of the life of this world; but what is with God is better and more lasting for those who believe and who upon their Lord rely
  42,37,"and those who avoid great sins and abominations, and who when they are wroth forgive"
  42,38,"and who assent to their Lord, and are steadfast in prayer, and whose affairs go by counsel amongst themselves, and who of what we have bestowed on them give alms"
  42,39,"and who, when wrong befalls them, help themselves"
  42,40,"For the recompence of evil is evil like unto it; but he who pardons and does well, then his reward is with God; verily, He loves not the unjust"
  42,41,"And he who helps himself after he has been wronged, for these - there is no way against them"
  42,42,The way is only against those who wrong men and are wanton in the earth without right; these - for them is grievous woe
  42,43,"But surely he who is patient and forgives,- verily, that is a determined affair"
  42,44,"But whomsoever God leads astray he has no patron after Him; and thou mayest see the unjust when they see the torment say, 'Is there no way to avert this"
  42,45,"and thou mayest see them exposed to it, humbled with abasement, looking with a stealthy glance. And those who believe shall say, 'Verily the losers are they who have lost themselves and their family's too upon the resurrection day!' Ay, verily, the unjust are in lasting torment"
  42,46,"And they shall have no patrons to help them beside God, and whomsoever God leads astray, there is no way for him"
  42,47,Assent to your Lord before the day comes of which there is no averting from God; there is no refuge for you on that day; and for you there is no denial
  42,48,"But if they turn aside, we have not sent thee to them as a guardian, thou hast only thy message to preach. And, verily, when we have made man taste of mercy from us he rejoices therein; but if there befall them an evil for what their hands have done before - then, verily, man is ungrateful"
  42,49,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, He creates what He pleases, He grants to whom He pleases females, and He grants to whom He pleases males, or He gives them in pairs, males and females"
  42,50,"and He makes whom He pleases barren; verily, He is knowing, powerful"
  42,51,"It is not for any mortal that God should speak to him, except by inspiration, or from behind a veil, or by sending an apostle and inspiring, by His permission, what He pleases; verily, He is high and wise"
  42,52,"And thus have we inspired thee by a spirit at our bidding; thou didst not know what the Book was, nor the faith: but we made it a light whereby we guide whom we will of our servants. And, verily, thou shalt surely be guided into the right way"
  42,53,"the way of God, whose is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth. Ay, to God affairs do tend"
  43,1,M
  43,2,By the perspicuous Book
  43,3,"verily, we have made it an Arabic Qur'an; haply ye will have some sense"
  43,4,"And it is in the Mother of the Book with us,- high and wise"
  43,5,"Shall we then push aside from you the Reminder, because ye are a people who are extravagant"
  43,6,How many prophets have we sent amongst those of yore
  43,7,and there never came to them a prophet but they did mock at him
  43,8,then we destroyed them - more valiant than these; and the example of those of yore passed away
  43,9,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, 'The mighty, the knowing One created them"
  43,10,"who made for you the earth a couch and placed for you therein roads, haply ye may be guided"
  43,11,and who sent down from the heaven water in due measure; and we raised up thereby a dead country; thus shall ye too be brought forth
  43,12,and who has created all species; and has made for you the ships and the cattle whereon to ride
  43,13,"that ye may settle yourselves on their backs; then remember the favour of your Lord when ye settled thereon, and say, 'Celebrated be the praises of Him who hath subjected this to us! We could not have got this ourselves"
  43,14,"and, verily, unto our Lord shall we return"
  43,15,"Yet they make for Him of His servants offspring; verily, man is surely obviously ungrateful"
  43,16,"Has He taken of what He creates daughters, and chosen sons for you"
  43,17,"Yet when the tidings are given any one of that which he strikes out as a similitude for the Merciful One, his face grows black and he is choked"
  43,18,"What! one brought up amongst ornaments, and who is always in contention without obvious cause"
  43,19,"And have they made the angels, who are the servants of the Merciful One, females? Were they witnesses of their creation? their witness shall be written down, and they shall be questioned"
  43,20,"and they say, 'Had the Merciful pleased we should never have worshipped them.' They have no knowledge of that, they only conjecture"
  43,21,Have we given them a book before it to which they might hold
  43,22,"Nay; they say, 'We found our fathers (agreed) upon a religion, and, verily, we are guided by their traces"
  43,23,"Thus, too, did we never send before thee to a city any warner, but the affluent ones thereof said, 'Verily, we found our fathers (agreed) upon a religion, and, verily, we are led by their traces"
  43,24,"Say, 'What! if I come to you with what is a better guide than what ye found your fathers agreed upon?' and they will say, 'Verily, we, in what ye are sent with disbelieve"
  43,25,"Then we took vengeance on them, and see how was the end of those who called the (apostles) liars"
  43,26,"When Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Verily, I am clear of all that ye serve"
  43,27,"except Him who created me; for, verily, He will guide me"
  43,28,"and he made it a word remaining among his posterity, that haply they might return"
  43,29,"Nay; but I let these (Meccans) and their fathers have enjoyment until the truth came to them, and an apostle"
  43,30,"And when the truth came to them they said, 'This is magic, and we therein do disbelieve"
  43,31,"And they say, 'Unless this Qur'an were sent down to a man great in the two cities"
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of thy Lord? We distribute amongst them their livelihood in the life of this world, and we exalt some of them above others in degrees, that some may take others into subjection; but the mercy of thy Lord is better than that which they amass"
  43,33,"And but that men would then have been one nation, we would have made for those who misbelieve in the Merciful One roofs of silver for their houses, and steps up thereto which they might mount"
  43,34,"and to their houses doors, and bedsteads on which they might recline"
  43,35,"and gilding,- for, verily, all that is a provision of the life of this world, but the hereafter is better with thy Lord for those who fear"
  43,36,"And whosoever turns from the reminder of the Merciful One, we will chain to him a devil, who shall be his mate"
  43,37,"and, verily these shall turn them from the path while they reckon that they are guided"
  43,38,"until when he comes to us he shall say, 'O, would that between me and thee there were the distance of the two orients, for an evil mate (art thou)"
  43,39,"But it shall not avail you on that day, since ye were unjust; verily, in the torment shall ye share"
  43,40,"What! canst thou make the deaf to hear, or guide the blind, or him who is in obvious error"
  43,41,Whether then we take thee off we will surely take vengeance on them
  43,42,"or whether we show thee that which we have promised them; for, verily, we have power over them"
  43,43,"Say, 'Dost thou hold to what is inspired thee?' verily, thou art in the right way"
  43,44,"and, verily, it is a reminder to thee and to thy people, but in the end they shall be asked"
  43,45,"And ask those whom we have sent before thee amongst the prophets, 'Did we make gods beside the Merciful One for them to serve"
  43,46,"We did send Moses with our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said, 'Verily, I am the apostle of the Lord of the worlds"
  43,47,"but when he came to them with our signs, lo, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"And we did not show them a sign, but it was greater than its fellow; and we seized them with the torment, haply they might turn"
  43,49,"And they said, 'O thou magician! pray for us to thy Lord, as He has engaged with thee: verily, we are guided"
  43,50,"And when we removed from them the torment, behold they broke their word"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed amongst his people; said he, 'O my people! is not the kingdom of Egypt mine? and these rivers that flow beneath me? What! can ye then not see"
  43,52,"Am I better than this fellow, who is contemptible, who can hardly explain himself"
  43,53,"Unless then bracelets of gold be cast upon him, or there come with him angels as his mates"
  43,54,"And he taught his people levity; and they obeyed him: verily, they were an abominable people"
  43,55,"And when they had annoyed us we took vengeance on them, and we drowned them all together"
  43,56,and we made them a precedent and an example to those after them
  43,57,"And when the son of Mary was set forth as a parable, behold thy people turned away from him"
  43,58,"and said, 'Are our gods better, or is he?' They did not set it forth to thee save for wrangling. Nay, but they are a contentious people"
  43,59,"He is but a servant whom we have been gracious to, and we have made him an example for the children of Israel"
  43,60,And if we please we can make of you angels in the earth to succeed you
  43,61,"And, verily, he is a sign of the Hour. Doubt not then concerning it, but follow this right way"
  43,62,"and let not the devil turn you away; verily, he is to you an open foe"
  43,63,"And when Jesus came with manifest signs he said, 'I am come to you with wisdom, and I will explain to you something of that whereon ye did dispute, then fear God, obey me"
  43,64,"verily, God, He is my Lord and your Lord, serve Him then, this is the right way"
  43,65,But the confederates disputed amongst themselves; and woe to those who are unjust from the torment of a grievous day
  43,66,Do they expect aught but that the Hour will come upon them suddenly while they do not perceive
  43,67,"Friends on that day shall be foes to each other, save those who fear"
  43,68,O my servants! there is no fear for you on that day; nor shall ye be grieved
  43,69,who believe in our signs and who are resigned
  43,70,"Enter ye into Paradise, ye and your wives, happy"
  43,71,"Dishes of gold and pitchers shall be sent round to them; therein is what souls desire, and eyes shall be delighted, and ye therein shall dwell for aye"
  43,72,for that is Paradise which ye are given as an inheritance for that which ye have done
  43,73,Therein shall ye have much fruit whereof to eat
  43,74,"Verily, the sinners are in the torment of hell to dwell for aye"
  43,75,"It shall not be intermitted for them, and they therein shall be confused"
  43,76,"We have not wronged them, but it was themselves they wronged"
  43,77,"And they shall cry out, 'O Malik! let thy lord make an end of us;' he shall say, 'Verily, ye are to tarry here"
  43,78,"We have brought you the truth, but most of you are averse from the truth"
  43,79,Have they arranged the affair? then will we arrange it too
  43,80,"Or do they reckon that we did not hear their secrets and their whispering? Nay, but our messengers are with them writing down"
  43,81,"Say, 'If the Merciful One has a son then am I the first to worship him"
  43,82,"Celebrated be the praise of the Lord of the heavens and the earth! the Lord of the throne, above all they attribute to Him"
  43,83,But leave them to ponder and to play until they meet that day of theirs which they are promised
  43,84,"He it is who is in the heaven a God and in the earth a God! and He is the wise, the knowing"
  43,85,"And blessed be he whose is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and what is between both, and His is the knowledge of the Hour, and unto Him shall ye be brought back"
  43,86,And those they call on beside Him shall not possess intercession except those only who bear witness for the truth and who do know
  43,87,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created them they shall surely say, 'God!' How then can they lie"
  43,88,"And what he says, 'O Lord, verily, these are a people who do not believe"
  43,89,"shun them then and say, \"Peace!\" for they at length shall know"
  44,1,M
  44,2,By the perspicuous Book
  44,3,"verily, we have sent it down on a blessed night;- verily, we had given warning"
  44,4,wherein is decided every wise affair
  44,5,"as an order from us. Verily, we were sending (apostles)"
  44,6,"a mercy from thy Lord; verily, He both hears and knows"
  44,7,"from the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between the two, if ye were but sure"
  44,8,"There is no god but He, He quickens and He kills - your Lord and the Lord of your fathers of yore"
  44,9,"Nay, they in doubt do play"
  44,10,But expect thou the day when the heaven shall bring obvious smoke
  44,11,to cover men - this is grievous torment
  44,12,"Our Lord! remove from us the torment; verily, we are believers"
  44,13,"How can they have the reminder (now), when they have had a plain apostle"
  44,14,"and when they turned their backs away from him and said, 'Taught! mad"
  44,15,"Verily, we will remove the torment a little, (but) ye will surely return"
  44,16,"On the day when we will assault with the great assault, verily, we will take vengeance"
  44,17,And we already tried the people of Pharaoh when there came to them a noble apostle
  44,18,"Send back to me God's servants; verily, I am to you a faithful apostle"
  44,19,"and, 'Exalt not yourselves above God; verily, I come to you with obvious authority"
  44,20,"And, verily, I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord, that ye stone me not"
  44,21,And if ye believe not in me then let me alone
  44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord, 'Verily, these are a sinful people"
  44,23,"So journey with my servants by night - verily, ye will be pursued"
  44,24,"But leave the sea in quiet - verily, they are a host to be drowned"
  44,25,How many gardens and springs have they left
  44,26,and corn lands and a noble place
  44,27,and comfort wherein they did enjoy themselves
  44,28,Thus - and we gave them for an inheritance to another people
  44,29,"And the heaven wept not for them, nor the earth, nor were they respited"
  44,30,But we saved the children of Israel from shameful woe
  44,31,"from Pharaoh; verily, he was haughty, one of the extravagant"
  44,32,"And we did choose them, wittingly, above the worlds"
  44,33,and we gave them signs wherein was an obvious trial
  44,34,"Verily, these say"
  44,35,It is but our first death
  44,36,"so bring our fathers, if ye do speak the truth"
  44,37,"Are they better than the people of Tubbah, and those before them? We destroyed them - verily, they were sinners"
  44,38,"Nor did we create the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two in sport"
  44,39,"we did but create them in truth, though most of them know it not"
  44,40,"Verily, the day of separation is their appointed term"
  44,41,"the day when master shall not avail client at all, nor shall they be helped"
  44,42,"save whomsoever God shall have mercy on; verily, He is the mighty, the merciful"
  44,43,"Verily, the Zaqqum tree"
  44,44,(shall be) the food of the sinful
  44,45,"as it were melting, shall it boil in their bellies"
  44,46,like the boiling of hot water
  44,47,Take him and hale him into the midst of hell
  44,48,then pour over his head the torment of hot water
  44,49,"Taste! verily, thou art the mighty, the honourable"
  44,50,"Verily, this is that whereon ye did dispute"
  44,51,"Verily, the pious shall be in a safe place"
  44,52,in gardens and springs
  44,53,they shall be clad in satin and stout silk face to face
  44,54,Thus!- and we will wed them to bright and large-eyed maids
  44,55,They shall call therein for every fruit in safety
  44,56,"They shall not taste therein of death save their first death, and we will keep them from the torment of hell"
  44,57,"Grace from thy Lord, that is the grand bliss"
  44,58,"And we have only made it easy for thy tongue, that haply they may be mindful"
  44,59,"Then watch thou; verily, they are watching too"
  45,1,M
  45,2,"A revelation of the Book from God, the mighty, the wise"
  45,3,"Verily, in the heavens and the earth are signs to those who believe"
  45,4,and in your creation and the beasts that are spread abroad are signs to a people who are sure
  45,5,"and in the alternation of night and day, and the provision that God has sent down from heaven and quickened thereby the earth after its death, and in the veering of the winds are signs unto a people who have sense"
  45,6,These are the signs of God which we recite to thee in truth; and in what new story after God and His signs will they believe
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"who hears God's signs sent to him, then persists in being big with pride as though he heard them not - so give him the glad-tidings of grievous woe"
  45,9,"and when he knows something of our signs takes them for a jest! These,- for them is shameful woe"
  45,10,"behind them is hell, and what they have earned shall not avail them aught, nor what they have taken besides God for patrons; and for them is mighty woe"
  45,11,"This is a guidance, and those who misbelieve in the signs of their Lord, for them is torment of a grievous plague"
  45,12,"God it is who subjects to you the sea that the ships may sail thereon at his bidding, and that ye may crave of His grace, and that haply ye may give thanks"
  45,13,"and He has subjected to you what is in the heavens and what is in the earth,- all from Him; verily, in that are signs unto a people who reflect"
  45,14,"Say to those who believe that they pardon those who hope not for God's days, that He may reward a people for that which they have earned"
  45,15,"Whosoever acts aright it is for his own soul, and whosoever does evil it is against it; then unto your Lord shall ye be returned"
  45,16,"And we did bring the children of Israel the Book and judgment and prophecy, and we provided them with good things, and preferred them above the worlds"
  45,17,"And we brought them manifest proofs of the affair, and they disputed not until after knowledge had come to them, through mutual envy. Verily, thy Lord will decide between them on the resurrection day concerning that whereon they did dispute"
  45,18,"Then we did set thee over a law concerning the affair: follow it then, and follow not the lusts of those who do not know"
  45,19,"Verily, they shall not avail thee against God at all; and, verily, the wrong-doers are patrons of each other, but God is the patron of those who fear"
  45,20,This is an insight for men and a guidance and a mercy to a people who are sure
  45,21,"Do those who commit evil deeds count that we will make them like those who, believe and work righteous deeds, equal in their life and their death?- ill it is they judge"
  45,22,"And God created the heavens and the earth in truth; and every soul shall be recompensed for that which it has earned, and they shall not be wronged"
  45,23,"Hast thou considered him who takes his lusts for his god, and God leads him astray wittingly, and has set a seal upon his hearing and his heart, and has placed upon his eyesight dimness? who then shall guide him after God? Will they not then mind"
  45,24,"They say, 'It is only our life in this world, we die and we live, and naught destroys us but time!' But they have no knowledge of this; they do but suspect"
  45,25,"And when our signs are rehearsed to them with evidences their only argument is to say, 'Bring our fathers, if ye speak the truth"
  45,26,"Say, 'God quickens you, then He kills you, then He will gather you unto the resurrection day, there is no doubt therein; but most men do not know"
  45,27,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and on the day when the Hour shall arise on that day shall those who call it vain be losers"
  45,28,"And thou shalt see each nation kneeling, each nation summoned to its book, 'Today are ye rewarded for that which ye have done"
  45,29,"This is our Book that speaketh to you with truth; verily, we have written down what ye have done"
  45,30,"But as to those who believe and do righteous deeds their Lord will make them enter into His mercy, that is the obvious bliss"
  45,31,"And as for those who misbelieve,- were not my signs recited to you and ye were too big with pride and ye were a sinful people"
  45,32,"And when it was said, 'Verily, the promise of God is true, and the Hour there is no doubt therein;' ye said, 'We know not what the Hour is, we only suspect, and we are not sure"
  45,33,"But there shall appear to them the evils of what they have done, and that shall encompass them at which they have been mocking"
  45,34,"And it shall be said, 'Today will we forget you as ye forgat the meeting of this day of yours, and your resort shall be the fire, and ye shall have no helpers"
  45,35,"That is because ye took the signs of God for a jest and the life of this world deceived you; wherefore today ye shall not be brought forth therefrom, neither shall ye be taken back into favour"
  45,36,"God's then is the praise, the Lord of the heavens and the Lord of the earth, the Lord of the worlds"
  45,37,"His is the grandeur in the heavens and the earth, and He is the mighty and the wise"
  46,1,M
  46,2,"The revelation of the Book from God the mighty, the wise"
  46,3,We have only created the heavens and the earth and what is between the two in truth and for an appointed time; but those who misbelieve from being warned do turn aside
  46,4,"Say, 'Have ye considered what ye call on beside God?' Show me what they have created of the earth? or have they share in the heavens? Bring me a book before this or a vestige of knowledge, if ye do tell the truth"
  46,5,But who is more in error than he who calls beside God on what will never answer him until the resurrection day and who are heedless of their calling
  46,6,and when men are gathered together are enemies of theirs and do deny their service
  46,7,"And when our evident signs are recited to them, those who misbelieve say of the truth when it comes to them, 'This is obvious magic"
  46,8,"Or do they say, 'He has forged it?' Say, 'If I have forged ye cannot obtain for me aught from God; He knows best what ye utter concerning it; He is witness enough between me and you, and He is the forgiving, the merciful"
  46,9,"Say, 'I am not an innovator among the apostles; nor do I know what will be done with me or with you if I follow aught but what I am inspired with; nor am I aught but a plain warner"
  46,10,"Say, 'Have ye considered, if it is from God and ye have disbelieved therein, and a witness from the children of Israel testifies to the conformity of it, and he believes while ye are too big with pride? Verily, God guides not the unjust people"
  46,11,"And those who misbelieve say of those who believe, 'If it had been good, they would not have been beforehand with us therein;' and when they are not guided thereby, then will they say, 'This is an old-fashioned lie"
  46,12,"But before it was the Book of Moses, a model and a mercy; and this is a book confirming it in Arabic language, to warn those who do wrong and as glad tidings to those who do well"
  46,13,"Verily, those who say, 'Our Lord is God,' and then keep straight, there is no fear for them, and they shall not be grieved"
  46,14,"These are the fellows of Paradise to dwell therein for aye, a recompence for that which they have done"
  46,15,"We have prescribed for man kindness towards his parents. His mother bore him with trouble and brought him forth with trouble; and the bearing of him and the weaning of him is thirty months; until, when he reaches puberty, and reaches forty years, he says, 'Lord! stir me up that I may be thankful for thy favours wherewith thou hast favoured me and my parents; and that I may do right to please Thee; and make it right for me in my offspring; verily, I turn repentant unto Thee, and, verily, I am of those resigned"
  46,16,"There are those from whom we accept the best of what they have done, and we pass over their offences - amongst the fellows of Paradise; the promise of truth which they have been promised"
  46,17,"But he who says to his parents, 'Fie upon you! Do ye promise me that I shall be brought forth when generations have passed away before me?' - then shall they both cry to God for help. Woe to thee! Believe! Verily, the promise of God is true. Then says he, 'This is but old folks' tales"
  46,18,"There are those against whom the sentence was due amongst the nations who have passed away before them of ginns and men; verily, they have been the losers"
  46,19,"and for all are degrees of what they have done, so that He may repay them their works, and they shall not be wronged"
  46,20,"And the day when those who misbelieve shall be exposed to the fire: 'Ye made away with your good things in your worldly life, and ye enjoyed them; wherefore today shall ye be rewarded with the torment of disgrace, for that ye were big with pride in the earth without the right, and for that ye did abomination"
  46,21,"Remember too the brother of 'Ad when he warned his people at El A'hqaf,- though warners have passed away before him and after him,- 'Serve not other than God; verily, I fear for you the torment of a mighty day"
  46,22,"They said, 'Hast thou come to us to turn us from our gods? then bring us what thou dost threaten us with, if thou art of those who speak the truth"
  46,23,"Said he, 'Knowledge is only with God: but I will preach to you that which I am sent with, though I see you are a people who are ignorant"
  46,24,"And when they saw a traversing cloud approaching their valleys they said, 'This is a cloud to give us rain.' 'Nay, but it is what ye sought to hasten on - a wind in which is grievous torment"
  46,25,it will destroy everything at the order of its Lord!' And in the morning naught was seen save their dwellings. Thus do we reward the sinful people
  46,26,"We had established them in what we have established you, and we made for them hearing and eyesight and hearts; but neither their hearing nor their eyesight nor their hearts availed them aught, since they did gainsay the signs of God, and that encompassed them whereat they had mocked"
  46,27,"And we destroyed the cities that are around you:- and we turned about the signs that haply they might return"
  46,28,"Why did not those help them, whom beside God they took for gods that could draw nigh to Him? Nay! they strayed away from them; for that was their lie and what they had forced"
  46,29,"And when we turned towards thee some of the ginn listening to the Qur'an, and when they were present at (the reading of) it, they said, 'Be silent!' and when it was over they turned back to their people, warning them"
  46,30,"Said they, 'O our people! verily, we have heard a book sent down after Moses, verifying what came before it, guiding to the truth, and unto the right way"
  46,31,"O our people! respond to God's crier and believe in Him, and He will pardon you your sins and will deliver you from grievous woe"
  46,32,"And whoso responds not to God's crier shall not frustrate Him in the earth, and shall not have any patrons beside Him:- these are in obvious error"
  46,33,"Did they not see that God who created the heavens and the earth, and was not wearied with creating them, is able to quicken the dead?- nay, verily, He is mighty over all"
  46,34,"And the day when those who misbelieve shall be exposed to the fire,- 'Is not this the truth?' they shall say, 'Yea, by our Lord!' He shall say, 'Then taste the torment for that ye did misbelieve"
  46,35,"Then do thou be patient, as the apostles endowed with a purpose were patient, and hasten not on (their, punishment). It shall be to them, on the day they see what they are threatened with, as though they had tarried but an hour of the day. A preaching this! Shall any perish but the people who work abomination"
  47,1,"Those who misbelieve and turn folk from God's way, He will make their works go wrong"
  47,2,"But those who believe and do right and believe in what is revealed to Mohammed,- and it is the truth from their Lord,- He will cover for them their offences and set right their mind"
  47,3,"That is because those who misbelieve follow falsehood, and those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. Thus does God set forth for men their parables"
  47,4,"And when ye meet those who misbelieve - then striking off heads until ye have massacred them, and bind fast the bonds! Then either a free grant (of liberty) or a ransom until the war shall have laid down its burdens. That!- but if God please He would conquer them - but (it is) that He may try some of you by the others. And those who are slain in God's cause, their works shall not go wrong"
  47,5,He will guide them and set right their mind
  47,6,and will make them enter into Paradise which He has told them of
  47,7,"O ye who believe! if ye help God, He will help you, and will make firm your footsteps"
  47,8,But as for those who misbelieve - confound them! and He will make their works go wrong
  47,9,That is because they were averse from what God has revealed; but their works shall be void
  47,10,Have they not journeyed through the land and seen how was the end of those before them? God destroyed them; and for the misbelievers is the like thereof
  47,11,"That is because God is the patron of those who believe, and because the misbelievers have no patron"
  47,12,"Verily, God causes those who believe and do right to enter into gardens beneath which rivers flow; but those who misbelieve enjoy themselves and eat as the cattle eat; but the fire is the resort for them"
  47,13,"How many a city, stronger than thy city which has driven thee out, have we destroyed, and there was none to help them"
  47,14,"Is he who rests upon a manifest sign from his Lord like him, the evil of whose works is made seemly to him, and who follow their lusts"
  47,15,"The similitude of Paradise which is promised to the pious,- in it are rivers of water without corruption, and rivers of milk, the taste whereof changes not, and rivers of wine delicious to those who drink; and rivers of honey clarified; and there shall they have all kinds of fruit and forgiveness from their Lord! (Is that) like him who dwells in the fire for aye? and who are given to drink boiling water that shall rend their bowels asunder"
  47,16,"Some of them there are who listen to thee, until when they go forth from thee they say to those who have been given the knowledge, 'What is this which he says now?' These are those on whose hearts God his set a stamp and who follow their lusts"
  47,17,"But those who are guided, He guides them the more, and gives them the due of their piety"
  47,18,"Do they wait for aught but the Hour, that it should come to them suddenly? The conditions thereof have come already; how, when it has come on them, can they have their reminder"
  47,19,"Know thou that there is no god but God; and ask pardon for thy sin and for the believers, men and women; for God knows your return and your resort"
  47,20,"Those who misbelieve say, 'Why has not a surah been revealed?' but when a decisive surah is revealed and fighting is mentioned therein, thou mayest see those in whose heart is sickness looking towards thee with the look of one fainting in death"
  47,21,"Preferable for them were obedience and a reasonable speech! But when the matter is determined on, then if they believed God it were better for them"
  47,22,"Would ye perhaps, if ye had turned back, have done evil in the land and severed the bonds of kinship"
  47,23,"It is these whom God has cursed, and has made them deaf, and has blinded their eyesight"
  47,24,Do they not peruse the Qur'an? or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Verily, those who turn their backs after the guidance that has been manifested to them - Satan induces them, but (God) lets them go on for a time"
  47,26,"That is for that they say to those who are averse from what God has revealed, 'We will obey you in part of the affair!' but God knows their secrets"
  47,27,"How will it be when the angels take their souls, smiting their faces and their backs"
  47,28,This is because they follow what angers God and are averse from His goodwill; and their works are void
  47,29,Do those in whose hearts is sickness reckon that God will not bring their malice forth
  47,30,"But did we please we would show thee them, and thou shouldst know them by their cognisances. But thou shalt know them by their distorting their speech, and God knows their works"
  47,31,But we will try you until we know those among you who fight strenuously and the patient; and we will try the reports concerning you
  47,32,"Verily, those who misbelieve and turn folks off God's path, and break with the Apostle after the guidance that has been manifested to them, cannot harm God at all, and their works shall be void"
  47,33,"O ye who believe! obey God, and obey the Apostle; and make not your works vain"
  47,34,"Verily, those who misbelieve and turn folks off God's path, and then die misbelievers, God will not pardon them"
  47,35,"Then faint not, nor cry for peace while ye have the upper hand; for God is with you and will not cheat you of your works"
  47,36,"The life of this world is but a play and a sport; but if ye believe and fear God, He will give you your hire"
  47,37,"He does not ask you for (all) your property; if He were to ask you for it and to press you, ye would be niggardly, and he would bring your malice out"
  47,38,"Here are ye called upon to expend in God's cause, and among you are some who are niggardly; and he who is niggardly is but niggardly against his own soul: but God is rich and ye are poor, and if ye turn your backs He will substitute another people in your stead, then they will not be like you"
  48,1,"Verily, we have given thee an obvious victory"
  48,2,"that God may pardon thee thy former and later sin, and may fulfil His favour upon thee, and guide thee in a right way"
  48,3,and that God may help thee with a mighty help
  48,4,"It is He who sent down His shechina into the hearts of the believers that they might have faith added to their faith;- and God's are the hosts of the heavens and the earth, and God is knowing, wise"
  48,5,"to make the believers, men and women, enter into gardens beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein for aye; and to cover for them their offences; for that with God is a grand bliss"
  48,6,"and to torment the hypocrites, men and women, and the idolaters, men and women, who think evil thoughts of God;- over them is a turn of evil fortune, and God will be wrath with them and curse them, and has prepared for them hell, and an evil journey shall it be"
  48,7,"God's are the hosts of the heavens and the earth, and God is mighty, wise"
  48,8,"Verily, we have sent thee as a witness, and a herald of glad tidings, and a warner"
  48,9,"that ye may believe in God and His Apostle, and may aid Him and revere Him and celebrate His praises morning and evening"
  48,10,"Verily, those who swear allegiance to thee do but swear allegiance to God;- God's hand is above their hands and whoso perjures himself does but perjure himself against himself; but he who fulfils what he has covenanted with God, God shall bring him mighty hire"
  48,11,"The desert Arabs who were left behind shall say, 'Our wealth and our people occupied us; ask pardon then for us!' - they speak with their tongues what is not in their hearts! Say, 'Who can control for you aught from God, if He wish you harm or wish you advantage?' Nay, God of what ye do is well aware"
  48,12,"Nay, ye thought that the Apostle and the believers would not ever return again to their families; that was made seemly in your hearts! and ye thought evil thoughts, and ye were a corrupt people"
  48,13,Whoso believes not in God and His Apostle - we have prepared for the unbelievers a blaze
  48,14,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and of the earth. He pardons whom He pleases, and torments whom He pleases; and God is forgiving, merciful"
  48,15,"Those who were left behind shall say when ye have gone forth to spoils that ye may take, 'Let us follow you;' they wish to change God's words. Say, 'Ye shall by no means follow us; thus did God say before!' They will say, 'Nay! but ye envy us!' Nay! they did not understand save a little"
  48,16,"Say to those desert Arabs who were left behind, 'Ye shall be called out against a people endowed with vehement valour, and shall fight them or they shall become Muslims. And if ye obey, God will give you a good hire; but if ye turn your backs, as ye turned your backs before, He will torment you with grievous woe"
  48,17,"There is no compulsion on the blind, and no compulsion on the lame, and no compulsion on the sick, but whoso obeys God and His Apostle, He will make him enter gardens beneath which rivers flow; but whoso turns his back He will torment with grievous woe"
  48,18,"God was well pleased with the believers when they did swear allegiance to thee beneath the tree; and He knew what was in their hearts, and He sent down His shechina upon them and rewarded them with a victory nigh at hand"
  48,19,"and many spoils for them to take; for God is mighty, wise"
  48,20,"God promised you many spoils and hastened this on for you, and restrained men's hands from you; and it may be a sign for the believers and guide you in a right way"
  48,21,and other (spoils) which ye could not gain; but God has encompassed them; for God is mighty over all
  48,22,"And had those who misbelieved fought you, they would have turned their backs; then they would have found neither patron nor helper"
  48,23,"God's course which has been followed before, and thou shalt find no change in the course of God"
  48,24,"He it was who restrained their hands from you, and your hands from them in the mid-valley of Mecca after He had given you the victory over them; for God on what ye do doth look"
  48,25,"Those who misbelieved and turned (you) away from the Sacred Mosque, and (turned away) the offering, kept from arriving at its destined place; and had it not been for believing men and believing women whom ye knew not, whom ye might have trampled on, and so a crime might have occurred to you on their account without your knowledge - that God may make whomsoever He pleases enter into His mercy. Had they been distinct from one another, we would have tormented those of them who misbelieved with grievous woe"
  48,26,"When those who misbelieved put in their hearts pique - the pique of ignorance - and God sent down His shechina upon His Apostle and upon the believers, and obliged them to keep to the word of piety, and they were most worthy of it and most suited for it; for God all things doth know"
  48,27,"God truly verified for His Apostle the vision that ye shall verity enter the Sacred Mosque, if God please, in safety with shaven heads or cut hair, ye shall not fear; for He knows what ye know not, and He has set for you, beside that, a victory nigh at hand"
  48,28,He it is who sent His Apostle with guidance and the religion of truth to set it above all religion; for God is witness enough
  48,29,"Mohammed is the Apostle of God, and those who are with Him are vehement against the misbelievers,- compassionate amongst themselves; thou mayest see them bowing down, adoring, craving grace from God and His goodwill,- their marks are in their faces from the effects of adoration;- that is their similitude in the law and their similitude in the gospel; as a seedling puts forth its sprouts and strengthens it, and grows stout, and straightens itself upon its stem, delighting the sower!- that the misbelievers may be angry at them;- God has promised those of them who believe and do right - forgiveness and a mighty hire"
  49,1,"O ye who believe! do not anticipate God and His Apostle, but fear God; verily, God both hears and knows"
  49,2,"O ye who believe! raise not your voices above the voice of the prophet, and do not speak loud to him as ye speak loud to one another, lest your works become vain, while ye do not perceive"
  49,3,"Verily, those who lower their voice before the Apostle of God, they are those whose hearts God has proved for piety, for them is forgiveness and a mighty hire"
  49,4,"Verily, those who cry out to thee from behind the inner chambers, most of them have no sense"
  49,5,"but did they wait until thou come out to them, it were better for them;- but God is forgiving, merciful"
  49,6,"O ye who believe! if there come to you a sinner with an information, then discriminate, lest ye fall upon a people in ignorance and on the morrow repent of what ye have done"
  49,7,"And know that among you is the Apostle of God; if he should obey you in many a matter ye would commit a sin; God has made faith beloved by you, and has made it seemly in your hearts, and has made misbelief and iniquity and rebellion hateful to you.- These are the rightly directed"
  49,8,"grace from God and favour! and God is knowing, wise"
  49,9,"And if the two parties of the believers quarrel, then make peace between them; and if one of the twain outrages the other, then fight the party that has committed the outrage until it return to God's bidding; and if it do return then make peace between them with equity, and be just; verily, God loves the just"
  49,10,"The believers are but brothers, so make peace between your two brethren and fear God, haply ye may obtain mercy"
  49,11,"O ye who believe! let not one class ridicule another who are perchance better than they; nor let women ridicule other women who are perchance better than they; and do not defame each other, nor call each other bad names - an ill name is iniquity after faith"
  49,12,"O ye who believe! carefully avoid suspicion; verily, some suspicion is a sin. And do not play the spy, nor backbite each other; would one of you like to eat his dead brother's flesh?- why! ye would abhor it! then fear God; verily, God is relentant, compassionate"
  49,13,"O ye folk! verily, we have created you of male and female, and made you races and tribes that ye may know each other. Verily, the most honourable of you in the sight of God is the most pious of you; verily, God is knowing, aware"
  49,14,"The desert Arabs say, 'We believe.' Say, 'Ye do not believe; but say, \"We have become Muslims;\" for the faith has not entered into your hearts: but if ye obey God and His Apostle He will not defraud you of your works at all: verily, God is forgiving, compassionate"
  49,15,"The believers are only those who believe in God and His Apostle, and then doubt not, but fight strenuously with their wealth and persons in God's cause - these are the truth-tellers"
  49,16,"Say, 'Will ye teach God your religion?' when God knows what is in the heavens and what is in the earth, and God all things doth know"
  49,17,"They deem that they oblige thee by becoming Muslims. Say, 'Nay! deem not that ye oblige me by your becoming Muslims! God obliges you, by directing you to the faith, if ye do speak the truth"
  49,18,"Verily, God knows the unseen things of the heavens and the earth, and God on what ye do doth look"